
00:00:01,235 --> 00:00:02,402
Narrator:
WELCOME TO THE SHARK TANK,

00:00:02,402 --> 00:00:05,239
WHERE ENTREPRENEURS
SEEK AN INVESTMENT

00:00:05,239 --> 00:00:08,008
TO START, GROW, OR SAVE
THEIR BUSINESS.

00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:10,143
I'M A FISHERMAN --
A DARN GOOD ONE.

00:00:10,143 --> 00:00:11,211
I'M PAT BOONE.

00:00:11,211 --> 00:00:13,013
OH!
HO, HO!

00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:14,114
WE CAME HERE
TO MAKE A DEAL.

00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:16,016
Narrator: IF THE SHARKS HEAR
A GREAT IDEA...

00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,084
WHOA!

00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:18,385
...THEY'LL INVEST
THEIR OWN MONEY...

00:00:18,385 --> 00:00:21,020
I WANT TO BRING THIS
TO THE AMERICAN MARKET.

00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:23,189
WHY DID NOBODY
THINK OF THIS BEFORE?
NOBODY'S AS SMART AS ME.

00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:25,057
Narrator: ...AND FIGHT
EACH OTHER FOR A DEAL.

00:00:25,057 --> 00:00:27,326
IF SOMEONE HAS A GOOD IDEA AND
COME IN HERE AND SELL US ON IT,

00:00:27,326 --> 00:00:28,995
THEY CAN GET
AN INVESTOR.
MARK, WE DON'T HAVE TO
AGREE WITH YOU.

00:00:28,995 --> 00:00:31,264
Narrator: BUT THE ENTREPRENEURS
MUST GET THE FULL AMOUNT

00:00:31,264 --> 00:00:34,000
THEY'RE ASKING FOR, OR THEY'LL
WALK AWAY WITH NOTHING.

00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,167
WHY AREN'T YOU TAKING
THE OFFER?

00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:37,136
DO YOU HAVE $200 MILLION
YOU'D LIKE TO PLOP DOWN?

00:00:38,004 --> 00:00:40,006
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE TEARS.

00:00:40,006 --> 00:00:42,375
YOU'RE TRYING TO BUILD A BAKERY
BEFORE TASTING THE CAKE.

00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,977
Narrator:
WHO ARE THE SHARKS?

00:00:46,345 --> 00:00:51,350
THEY'RE SELF-MADE
BUSINESS EXPERTS WORTH BILLIONS.

00:00:51,350 --> 00:00:54,287
KEVIN O'LEARY IS
A SHREWD VENTURE CAPITALIST

00:00:54,287 --> 00:00:56,122
WHO MADE HIS FORTUNE

00:00:56,122 --> 00:00:58,057
SELLING A CHILDREN'S
EDUCATIONAL COMPANY

00:00:58,057 --> 00:01:00,359
FOR OVER $4 BILLION.

00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:04,296
DAYMOND JOHN DOMINATED
THE FASHION WORLD WITH FUBU.

00:01:04,296 --> 00:01:07,299
NOW HE'S THE BRANDING EXPERT
BEHIND MULTIPLE GLOBAL BRANDS

00:01:07,299 --> 00:01:09,334
GENERATING BILLIONS IN SALES.

00:01:10,335 --> 00:01:13,238
ROBERT HERJAVEC, SON OF
AN IMMIGRANT FACTORY WORKER,

00:01:13,238 --> 00:01:14,372
FOUNDED ONE OF

00:01:14,372 --> 00:01:18,276
THE WORLD'S PREEMINENT
CYBER-SECURITY FIRMS.

00:01:18,276 --> 00:01:22,314
LORI GREINER, THE QUEEN OF QVC,
HOLDS OVER 100 PATENTS

00:01:22,314 --> 00:01:24,082
AND HAS LAUNCHED
OVER 400 PRODUCTS,

00:01:24,082 --> 00:01:27,252
GROSSING OVER A HALF A BILLION
DOLLARS IN SALES.

00:01:27,252 --> 00:01:31,456
AND MARK CUBAN,
RENOWNED BILLIONAIRE TECH MOGUL

00:01:31,456 --> 00:01:35,460
AND THE OUTSPOKEN OWNER
OF THE DALLAS MAVERICKS.

00:01:41,132 --> 00:01:45,002
FIRST UP IS
A REVOLUTIONARY NEW WAY

00:01:45,002 --> 00:01:46,303
TO POWER TRANSPORTATION.

00:01:49,173 --> 00:01:50,274
OH!

00:01:50,274 --> 00:01:51,342
HO, HO!

00:01:51,342 --> 00:01:52,943
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:01:54,178 --> 00:01:56,313
Tucker: HELLO, SHARKS.

00:01:56,313 --> 00:01:58,415
MY NAME IS
ETHAN TUCKER,

00:01:58,415 --> 00:02:00,985
AND I'M FROM THE BEAUTIFUL
GREEN MOUNTAINS

00:02:00,985 --> 00:02:03,087
OF BRATTLEBORO, VERMONT.

00:02:03,087 --> 00:02:05,155
AND I'M PAT BOONE,
AGING SINGER

00:02:05,155 --> 00:02:08,359
AND, LIKE YOU,
A LIFELONG ENTREPRENEUR.

00:02:08,359 --> 00:02:11,996
OUR COMPANY
IS ZERO POLLUTION MOTORS,

00:02:11,996 --> 00:02:14,365
AND WE ARE SEEKING
$5 MILLION

00:02:14,365 --> 00:02:17,301
IN EXCHANGE
FOR 50% OF OUR COMPANY.

00:02:17,301 --> 00:02:20,404
OUR GOAL
IS TO GIVE TO AMERICA

00:02:20,404 --> 00:02:25,075
THE LEANEST, CLEANEST, GREENEST
FORM OF AUTO TRANSPORTATION

00:02:25,075 --> 00:02:28,311
EVER TO HIT
OUR CROWDED, POLLUTED CITIES.

00:02:28,311 --> 00:02:31,447
SO, SHARKS,
IT IS MY GREAT PLEASURE

00:02:31,447 --> 00:02:34,217
TO INTRODUCE TO YOU...

00:02:34,217 --> 00:02:35,284
THE AIR CAR.

00:02:35,284 --> 00:02:37,086
[ LAUGHS ]
Herjavec: THE WHAT?

00:02:37,086 --> 00:02:39,222
THE CAR THAT RUNS
ON AIR.

00:02:39,222 --> 00:02:40,289
WOW.

00:02:40,289 --> 00:02:43,026
THAT'S RIGHT, AIR,
BUT HIGHLY COMPRESSED AIR.

00:02:43,026 --> 00:02:45,461
[ LAUGHTER ]
THERE IT IS.

00:02:45,461 --> 00:02:48,297
AIR, OF COURSE,
IS THE LEAST EXPENSIVE,

00:02:48,297 --> 00:02:49,432
MOST READILY AVAILABLE,

00:02:49,432 --> 00:02:51,434
AND THE MOST ENVIRONMENTALLY
PERFECT FUEL

00:02:51,434 --> 00:02:53,236
THAT WILL EVER BE,

00:02:53,236 --> 00:02:55,304
AND THE AirPod
USES COMPRESSED AIR

00:02:55,304 --> 00:02:57,373
TO DRIVE THE PISTONS
IN THE ENGINE.

00:02:57,373 --> 00:02:59,075
WHAT?
IT IS FAR SUPERIOR

00:02:59,075 --> 00:03:01,244
TO THE ELECTRIC CAR

00:03:01,244 --> 00:03:03,112
BECAUSE OF ITS PRICE

00:03:03,112 --> 00:03:05,381
AND IT ELIMINATES THE NEED
FOR BATTERIES,

00:03:05,381 --> 00:03:08,083
WHICH ARE EXPENSIVE
AND INEFFICIENT.

00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:09,084
LOOK AT THAT THING GO.

00:03:09,084 --> 00:03:11,053
NOW, THIS IS
A PICTURE WE TOOK,

00:03:11,053 --> 00:03:13,188
WHICH IS NOT
TOTALLY LIFE-SIZE.

00:03:13,188 --> 00:03:15,991
THIS IS JUST
THE FIRST PROTOTYPE.

00:03:15,991 --> 00:03:17,392
AND, SO, HOW MANY
WANT TO JOIN US

00:03:17,392 --> 00:03:20,128
FOR A DAZZLING RIDE
INTO THE FUTURE?

00:03:20,128 --> 00:03:23,298
LOOK, PAT, I KNOW YOU'VE SOLD
OVER 40 MILLION RECORDS.

00:03:23,298 --> 00:03:24,966
THEY SAY.

00:03:24,966 --> 00:03:26,168
I DIDN'T GET PAID THAT MANY,
BUT YES.
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:03:26,168 --> 00:03:27,369
WHAT WAS YOUR BIGGEST HIT?
I'M JUST CURIOUS.

00:03:27,369 --> 00:03:29,237
"LOVE LETTERS
IN THE SAND."

00:03:30,172 --> 00:03:32,140
YOU KNOW, I LOVE CARS.
I DO.

00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:33,241
I RACE CARS.

00:03:33,241 --> 00:03:35,243
WHAT MADE YOU THINK

00:03:35,243 --> 00:03:37,145
I WOULDN'T WANT TO GET IN IT
AND TRY IT?

00:03:37,145 --> 00:03:38,180
[ LAUGHS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:39,314
WELL --
WHY ISN'T IT HERE?

00:03:39,314 --> 00:03:41,249
I KNOW, WE WOULD LIKE YOU
TO BE IN IT,

00:03:41,249 --> 00:03:43,018
AND THERE'S
SEVERAL REASONS.

00:03:43,018 --> 00:03:45,287
ONE IS THAT THE CAR, TO COME
INTO THE UNITED STATES,

00:03:45,287 --> 00:03:47,089
HAS TO MEET
SAFETY STANDARDS.

00:03:47,089 --> 00:03:48,290
IT HAS IN EUROPE
ALREADY.

00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:50,357
OH, SO THIS IS ALREADY
A PRODUCTION CAR.

00:03:50,357 --> 00:03:52,126
IT IS MOVING
INTO PRODUCTION.

00:03:52,126 --> 00:03:53,360
AND YOU'VE BOUGHT
THE LICENSE TO IT,

00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,995
OR YOU WANT TO BUY
THE LICENSING?

00:03:54,995 --> 00:03:56,430
WE HAVE THE RIGHT
TO BUILD THE FIRST PLANT

00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:58,132
IN THE UNITED STATES.

00:03:58,132 --> 00:03:59,366
SO, ETHAN, WHERE --
Greiner:
IN THE UNITED STATES?

00:03:59,366 --> 00:04:01,168
YOU SHOULD EXPLAIN
HOW IT'S POWERED.

00:04:01,168 --> 00:04:02,169
IS THIS COMPRESSED AIR?

00:04:02,169 --> 00:04:03,404
IT IS COMPRESSED AIR.

00:04:03,404 --> 00:04:05,406
IT IS NOT
A COMBUSTION PRINCIPLE.

00:04:05,406 --> 00:04:08,008
IT IS
A PROPULSION PRINCIPLE.

00:04:08,008 --> 00:04:11,011
NOW, A CRUDE WAY TO ILLUSTRATE
WOULD BE BLOW UP A BALLOON.

00:04:11,011 --> 00:04:11,445
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

00:04:11,445 --> 00:04:13,380
PBBBBTH.
IT TAKES OFF.

00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:15,416
PAT, HOW FAST DOES
THE LUNCHBOX ON WHEELS GO?

00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:17,118
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:04:17,118 --> 00:04:19,453
IT WOULD GO ABOUT
50 MILES AN HOUR, TOPS.

00:04:19,453 --> 00:04:21,355
Herjavec:
IT IS SELF-PERPETUATING?

00:04:21,355 --> 00:04:24,291
IN OTHER WORDS, IS THERE A
CERTAIN AMOUNT OF COMPRESSED AIR

00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:27,061
WITHIN THE VEHICLE TO LAST
A CERTAIN AMOUNT OF TIME?

00:04:27,061 --> 00:04:30,096
YOU PLUG IN THE AirPod
TO ANY OUTLET...

00:04:30,096 --> 00:04:32,332
OKAY.
...AND IT TAKES
FOUR HOURS TO CHARGE.

00:04:32,332 --> 00:04:35,335
THE MOTOR CHARGES ITSELF.
IT COMPRESSES THE AIR.

00:04:35,335 --> 00:04:37,303
HOW LONG DOES IT LAST?

00:04:37,303 --> 00:04:40,306
YOU HAVE
100 MILES RANGE.

00:04:40,306 --> 00:04:42,008
I'M A CONSUMER.

00:04:42,008 --> 00:04:43,243
I'M COMING TO A STORE TO BUY
AN AIR CAR OR A BATTERY CAR.

00:04:43,243 --> 00:04:44,344
OKAY.
YEAH.

00:04:44,344 --> 00:04:45,445
TELL ME WHY
I'M GONNA BUY THE AIR CAR.

00:04:45,445 --> 00:04:47,046
THERE'S ONE
BIG DIFFERENCE.

00:04:47,046 --> 00:04:48,081
TELL ME.

00:04:48,081 --> 00:04:49,182
OTHER THAN THE PRICE --
TELL ME!

00:04:49,182 --> 00:04:50,083
I'LL TELL YOU!

00:04:50,083 --> 00:04:51,317
[ GREINER LAUGHS ]

00:04:51,317 --> 00:04:53,319
THE DIFFERENCE IS, IF THERE'S
A COMPRESSOR AT A GAS STATION,

00:04:53,319 --> 00:04:55,054
JUST LIKE YOU FILL UP
YOUR TIRES,

00:04:55,054 --> 00:04:57,423
YOU CAN FILL UP YOUR CAR
IN FOUR MINUTES.
WHAT'S THE COST?

00:04:57,423 --> 00:04:59,425
$10,000.

00:04:59,425 --> 00:05:01,094
$10,000 FOR
THE AIR CAR?

00:05:01,094 --> 00:05:03,062
THE CAR COSTS $10,000?

00:05:03,062 --> 00:05:04,364
THE CAR COSTS $10,000?
THAT'S IT?
YEAH.

00:05:04,364 --> 00:05:06,266
THAT'S IT!
SOMETHING'S WRONG HERE.

00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:08,301
NO, BECAUSE
IT'S VERY SIMPLY MADE.

00:05:08,301 --> 00:05:11,937
THE INVENTOR -- YOU MAY KNOW
THE NAME -- GUY NEGRE.

00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:14,306
YEAH, DOESN'T -- ISN'T HE
THE GUY WHO DEVELOPED THE...

00:05:14,306 --> 00:05:15,340
TITANIUM PISTON.

00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:17,209
TITANIUM
FOR A LIGHTER MOTOR.

00:05:17,209 --> 00:05:19,344
HE'S GOT 150 PATENTS.
HE KNOWS DEVELOPMENT.

00:05:19,344 --> 00:05:20,379
SO HE'S A REAL CAR GUY.

00:05:20,379 --> 00:05:22,047
HE LOVES CARS.
RIGHT.

00:05:22,047 --> 00:05:23,348
WHAT WOULD IT COST FOR YOU
TO BRING YOUR CAR HERE?

00:05:23,348 --> 00:05:25,184
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
MANUFACTURE IT HERE, I THOUGHT.

00:05:25,184 --> 00:05:27,319
WE'RE GONNA MANUFACTURE
IN HAWAII.
YEAH,
WE'RE GONNA MANUFACTURE --

00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:29,121
WE'RE BRINGING IT
TO THE UNITED STATES.
HAWAII?

00:05:29,121 --> 00:05:31,290
THE $5 MILLION IS FOR
A PLANT TO BUI--

00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:33,358
REGIONAL PLANT
TO BUILD THE CARS.

00:05:33,358 --> 00:05:34,359
WHY HAWAII?

00:05:34,359 --> 00:05:36,995
HAWAII IS A SORT OF
ENCLOSED COMMUNITY

00:05:36,995 --> 00:05:38,330
WHERE THEY HAVE
POLLUTION PROBLEMS,

00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:41,099
THEY HAVE
HIGH COST OF GAS,

00:05:41,099 --> 00:05:43,101
AND IT'S MORE OF
A CONTROLLED PLACE.

00:05:43,101 --> 00:05:44,403
PART OF THE CONCEPT
OF THE COMPANY

00:05:44,403 --> 00:05:47,005
IS NOT A BIG
DETROIT-TYPE PLANT.

00:05:47,005 --> 00:05:49,041
IT IS REGIONAL PLANTS,
SMALL PLANTS,

00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:52,077
BUILDING CARS
FOR THAT AREA.

00:05:52,077 --> 00:05:53,411
PAT, CAN YOU SHARE
WHAT IT'S MADE OUT OF?

00:05:53,411 --> 00:05:56,380
FIBERGLASS, POLYURETHANE,
AND RESIN.

00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,049
YOU CAN JUMP ON A DOOR,

00:05:58,049 --> 00:06:00,084
AND IT WON'T BEND
LIKE A REGULAR CAR.

00:06:00,084 --> 00:06:02,220
BUT WHAT ABOUT
IN A CRASH TEST?

00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:06,991
SO, WE CAN'T PASS A CRASH TEST
UNTIL WE'VE CRASHED A CAR,

00:06:06,991 --> 00:06:08,326
AND WE DON'T WANT TO CRASH
A PROTOTYPE.

00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:11,095
WE ONLY HAVE
THREE PROTOTYPES,

00:06:11,095 --> 00:06:12,363
SO WE WOULD BE CRASHING --

00:06:12,363 --> 00:06:15,099
TESTING A CAR
THAT WAS BUILT FROM SCRATCH.

00:06:15,099 --> 00:06:18,135
$5 MILLION TO BUILD YOUR FACTORY
IN HAWAII.

00:06:18,135 --> 00:06:20,037
THEN YOU HAVE TO MARKET IT,
RIGHT?
YEAH, YEAH.

00:06:20,037 --> 00:06:22,139
AND NOT ONLY DO YOU HAVE TO
LET PEOPLE KNOW IT EXISTS,

00:06:22,139 --> 00:06:24,408
YOU HAVE TO CONVINCE THEM
THAT THEY CAN TRUST IT.
YEAH, YEAH.

00:06:24,408 --> 00:06:26,477
THAT'S EXACTLY WHY
WE'RE IN HAWAII --

00:06:26,477 --> 00:06:28,112
BECAUSE WE WANT TO DO IT
SLOWLY.

00:06:28,112 --> 00:06:31,115
OKAY, SO YOUR LICENSE IS NOT FOR
ALL OF THE UNITED STATES

00:06:31,115 --> 00:06:32,350
ON AN EXCLUSIVE BASIS.
NO, IT'S FOR
THIS ONE PLANT.

00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,151
THE COMPANY'S CALLED MDI,

00:06:34,151 --> 00:06:37,420
AND THEY'VE JUST MADE A DEAL
WITH TATA MOTORS FOR INDIA,

00:06:37,420 --> 00:06:42,058
A $30 MILLION DEAL,
SO THEY WRAPPED UP INDIA.

00:06:42,058 --> 00:06:45,195
AND THE MDI COMPANY
HAS ALL OF FRANCE.

00:06:45,195 --> 00:06:48,098
SO, THEY'RE ONLY ISSUING
A COUPLE PLANTS PER TERRITORY?
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

00:06:48,098 --> 00:06:49,232
Boone:
AREAS, REGIONS, YEAH.

00:06:49,232 --> 00:06:51,301
JUST SO WE CAN BE CRYSTAL-CLEAR
ON THE OPPORTUNITY.

00:06:51,301 --> 00:06:53,003
YEAH.

00:06:53,003 --> 00:06:55,372
I'M ASSUMING THAT I BECOME A 50%
PARTNER IN A PLANT IN HAWAII

00:06:55,372 --> 00:06:58,208
AND THAT I OWN
THAT ENTIRE TERRITORY.

00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:01,311
EVERY CAR SOLD
ON EVERY ISLAND IN HAWAII

00:07:01,311 --> 00:07:03,013
IS COMING FROM THAT PLANT.

00:07:03,013 --> 00:07:04,347
IS THAT TRUE?
YES.

00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:06,116
BUT IF SOMEBODY BUILDS A PLANT
IN SAN FRANCISCO

00:07:06,116 --> 00:07:07,284
AND SHIPS A CAR
INTO MY TERRITORY --

00:07:07,284 --> 00:07:10,053
NOT ALLOWED.
CANNOT HAPPEN.

00:07:10,053 --> 00:07:12,222
GUYS, GUYS, I'M GONNA
SIMPLIFY THINGS HERE, RIGHT?

00:07:12,222 --> 00:07:15,225
THE SMART THING, AS AN INVESTOR,
IS TO JUST WATCH WHAT HAPPENS

00:07:15,225 --> 00:07:16,392
WITH TATA MOTORS IN INDIA,

00:07:16,392 --> 00:07:20,095
SEE HOW IT SELLS,
LOOK AT THEIR EXPERIENCE,

00:07:20,095 --> 00:07:23,165
AND THEN, IF IT GOES GOOD, WATCH
SOMEBODY ELSE OPEN UP A PLANT --

00:07:23,165 --> 00:07:25,968
YOU'RE TOO LATE. THIS IS
HAPPENING RIGHT NOW.
THIS WAVE IS CRESTING.

00:07:25,968 --> 00:07:28,103
IF IT WAS HAPPENING RIGHT NOW,
YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

00:07:28,103 --> 00:07:30,239
YOU'D ALREADY HAVE THE MONEY
AND HAVE THE PLANT OPEN.
NO, IT'S --

00:07:30,239 --> 00:07:31,340
GUYS, I'M OUT.

00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:35,377
THE STRATEGY
OF TRYING TO BUY A LICENSE

00:07:35,377 --> 00:07:38,180
FOR A SINGLE PLANT
IS ALMOST LUDICROUS.

00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:40,416
IF YOU CAN'T TIE UP
AN ENTIRE REGION,

00:07:40,416 --> 00:07:44,119
YOU'RE BUYING THE RIGHT
TO BECOME A DEALER IN HAWAII.

00:07:44,119 --> 00:07:47,156
YOU'VE GOT TO LOCK UP
ALL OF UNITED STATES.

00:07:47,156 --> 00:07:49,391
DO YOU HAVE $200 MILLION YOU'D
LIKE TO PLOP DOWN FOR THAT?

00:07:49,391 --> 00:07:50,426
YOU BECOME THE PIONEERS.

00:07:50,426 --> 00:07:52,328
YOU ESTABLISH A REGION
FOR $5 MILLION,

00:07:52,328 --> 00:07:53,395
PROVE THE MODEL,

00:07:53,395 --> 00:07:55,331
AND SOMEBODY ELSE SCOOPS
THE REST OF THE COUNTRY.

00:07:55,331 --> 00:07:57,232
THAT MAKES NO SENSE TO ME
AS AN INVESTOR.

00:07:57,232 --> 00:07:58,232
WE WILL BE THE FIRST.

00:07:58,232 --> 00:08:00,068
I GET IT --
BUT NOT THE LAST.

00:08:00,068 --> 00:08:01,402
AND WE HAVE
THE INSIDE CONNECTION TO MDI.

00:08:01,402 --> 00:08:04,005
I CAN GO TO MDI
AND SIMPLY DO A DEAL RIGHT NOW,

00:08:04,005 --> 00:08:05,206
WITHOUT YOU,
FOR NEW YORK.

00:08:05,206 --> 00:08:08,142
WELL, HERE'S MY ANSWER
TO THAT.

00:08:08,142 --> 00:08:10,011
TRY, BECAUSE OUR --

00:08:10,011 --> 00:08:12,180
WHY, 'CAUSE THEY DON'T WANT
MY CAR IN NEW YORK OR MY MONEY?

00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,448
NO, THEY DON'T WANT TO BE
DOUBLE-CROSSED.

00:08:13,448 --> 00:08:15,183
THERE'S A TRUST FACTOR.
OUR COMPANY --

00:08:15,183 --> 00:08:18,119
YOU COULD NOT GO DIRECTLY
TO GUY AND SAY,

00:08:18,119 --> 00:08:20,054
"I'M GONNA PLOP DOWN
$5 MILLION,"

00:08:20,054 --> 00:08:21,956
AND COMPLETELY
DOUBLE-CROSS US.

00:08:21,956 --> 00:08:23,091
Herjavec:
YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:08:23,091 --> 00:08:26,427
PUSH COMES TO SHOVE,
THEIR COMPANY GETS IN TROUBLE

00:08:26,427 --> 00:08:30,031
AND KEVIN COMES ALONG WITH A
$5 MILLION OFFER FOR THE RIGHTS.

00:08:30,031 --> 00:08:33,201
$5 MILLION, TO GUY,
IS SMALL POTATOES.

00:08:33,201 --> 00:08:36,304
THE WAY TO MAKE THIS WORK
IS TO SIT DOWN

00:08:36,304 --> 00:08:39,207
AND COME UP WITH
A NATIONAL STRATEGY

00:08:39,207 --> 00:08:41,074
FOR THE ENTIRE U.S. MARKET

00:08:41,074 --> 00:08:43,977
AND THEN PACKAGE THAT UP
AND BRING IT TO INVESTORS.

00:08:43,977 --> 00:08:46,146
YOU'RE TRYING TO BUILD A BAKERY
BEFORE TASTING THE CAKE.

00:08:46,146 --> 00:08:49,049
THAT'S RIGHT, BUT WE'RE
GONNA ALLOW OTHERS
TO TASTE THE CAKE.

