SHAUNA,
DO YOU HAVE SALES?

00:18:04,391 --> 00:18:08,128
THE TOTAL SALES
ARE $135,000.

00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:09,329
THAT'S IMPRESSIVE.

00:18:09,329 --> 00:18:11,364
Greiner: JUST IN WHOLE FOODS,
OR ARE YOU OTHER PLACES?

00:18:11,364 --> 00:18:14,968
WE ARE IN OVER 350
BRICK-AND-MORTAR LOCATIONS.

00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:16,202
WHY AREN'T YOU IN
MORE WHOLE FOODS?

00:18:16,202 --> 00:18:17,270
OH, SO, WE ARE.

00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:19,205
SO, THAT'S PART OF
WHY I NEED YOU GUYS,

00:18:19,205 --> 00:18:22,107
BECAUSE I WANT TO BRING ON
A BROKER.

00:18:22,107 --> 00:18:25,110
AND, SO, WE HAVE THEM
ON THE DISTRIBUTION SIDE

00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:27,146
FOR A VERY
SHOESTRING BUDGET.

00:18:27,146 --> 00:18:28,981
WHAT DOES IT COST
TO MAKE A BAR,

00:18:28,981 --> 00:18:30,149
AND WHAT DO YOU SELL IT FOR?
YEAH, WHAT DO YOU SELL IT FOR?

00:18:30,149 --> 00:18:32,384
THE HARD COST --
THAT'S, LIKE, SHIPPING, PALLET,

00:18:32,384 --> 00:18:35,287
GET IT TO MY WAREHOUSE --
WAS $1.09 PER BAR.

00:18:35,287 --> 00:18:38,157
SO IT'S $1.09 PER BAR.
WHAT DO YOU SELL IT FOR?

00:18:38,157 --> 00:18:41,160
AND, SO, RETAIL IS $2.99.

00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,261
SEEMS LOW.

00:18:42,261 --> 00:18:45,164
WE'RE WORKING ON OUR MARGINS.
WE'RE AT 25%.

00:18:45,164 --> 00:18:47,967
AND ANOTHER REASON
I NEED YOU GUYS --

00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:52,004
'CAUSE I WOULD LIKE YOU TO HELP
ME NEGOTIATE OUR BUYING POWER.

00:18:52,004 --> 00:18:53,238
WHAT ARE YOUR SALES ONLINE,
SHAUNA?

00:18:53,238 --> 00:18:55,407
OUR ONLINE SALES
ARE ABOUT $45,000.

00:18:55,407 --> 00:19:00,212
YOU HAVE GREAT ENERGY,
BUT I HAVE TO BE HONEST.
OKAY.

00:19:00,212 --> 00:19:02,214
I DON'T LIKE
THE TASTE OF THE BAR.

00:19:02,214 --> 00:19:05,216
I JUST REALLY DON'T LIKE
THE TASTE OF THE BAR...
AND SOME PEOPLE DON'T.

00:19:05,216 --> 00:19:07,385
...AND, SO, FOR THAT REASON,
I MUST GO OUT.

00:19:09,988 --> 00:19:10,989
OKAY.

00:19:10,989 --> 00:19:13,057
AND, YOU KNOW,
I THINK, AS WE GROW,

00:19:13,057 --> 00:19:15,994
WE CAN MAYBE TWEAK THE TASTE,
YOU KNOW --

00:19:15,994 --> 00:19:17,228
SHAUNA,
I LIKE THE TASTE.

00:19:17,228 --> 00:19:19,130
IT TASTES BETTER THAN
SOME OF THE OTHER STUFF.

00:19:19,130 --> 00:19:20,231
BUT LET'S
GO BACK TO THIS.

00:19:20,231 --> 00:19:22,200
IS THIS
YOUR FULL-TIME JOB?

00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,267
IT IS.

00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:25,970
THE ONLY THING I DO
ON THURSDAY AFTERNOONS

00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:27,238
IS SEE MY DENTAL PATIENTS.

00:19:28,339 --> 00:19:29,941
YOU'RE A DENTAL HYGIENIST.

00:19:29,941 --> 00:19:31,042
WELL, WHAT ABOUT
TEACHING CLASSES?

00:19:31,042 --> 00:19:32,377
OH, JUST IN THE MORNING,
EARLY.

00:19:34,045 --> 00:19:37,248
'CAUSE I HAVE TO START AROUND
4:00 IN THE MORNING.

00:19:37,248 --> 00:19:39,050
YOU KNOW, I NEED HELP...

00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:41,252
YOU THINK?
...BECAUSE WE'VE CREATED
A NICE FOUNDATION, MORE BARS,

00:19:41,252 --> 00:19:43,021
AND SO I CAN'T BACKTRACK.
SHAUNA --

00:19:43,021 --> 00:19:45,122
I THINK -- I THINK YOU'RE
SPREADING YOURSELF TOO THIN,

00:19:45,122 --> 00:19:46,323
BUT YOU'RE ALSO
JUST TRYING TO FIGURE IT OUT.

00:19:46,323 --> 00:19:47,324
I HONESTLY AM.

00:19:47,324 --> 00:19:49,292
AND I'M LIKE,
DON'T GIVE UP ON ME,

00:19:49,292 --> 00:19:52,029
BECAUSE YOU GUYS
HAVE ALL BEEN THERE.

00:19:52,029 --> 00:19:55,065
YOU KNOW -- YOU KNOW THE
DETERMINATION AND WHAT IT TAKES.

00:19:55,065 --> 00:19:57,200
[ Voice breaking ]
AND I KNOW I AM BUSY.

00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,368
I AM.

00:19:58,368 --> 00:20:01,004
BUT I WON'T LET IT DIE,

00:20:01,004 --> 00:20:04,241
BECAUSE DR. CORDAIN WAS BEING
COURTED BY TWO MAJOR COMPANIES,

00:20:04,241 --> 00:20:06,410
ONE IN CHICAGO --
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE TEARS.

00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:08,111
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

00:20:08,111 --> 00:20:10,213
ONE IN CHICAGO
AND ONE IN BOSTON.

00:20:10,213 --> 00:20:15,385
AND HE TRUSTS US, BECAUSE
WE WILL DO RIGHT BY HIM.

00:20:15,385 --> 00:20:18,188
AND, YOU KNOW, IT MIGHT TAKE
A LITTLE BIT LONGER

00:20:18,188 --> 00:20:20,424
WITHOUT YOU GUYS,
BUT I'M NOT GONNA STOP.

00:20:20,424 --> 00:20:23,093
BUT I WOULD LOVE TO HAVE YOU
BY MY SIDE --

00:20:23,093 --> 00:20:25,961
YOU KNOW, WHOEVER BELIEVES IN
THE PALEO DIET.

00:20:25,961 --> 00:20:27,196
SHAUNA, I'VE BEEN
QUIETLY LISTENING TO YOU.

00:20:27,196 --> 00:20:28,264
I KNOW.
I'M SCARED OF THAT.

00:20:28,264 --> 00:20:30,232
YOU HAVE A LOT OF ENERGY,
AND IT SPRAYS OUT OF YOU

00:20:30,232 --> 00:20:33,035
LIKE THE SUN IN 360 DIRECTIONS,
RIGHT?

00:20:33,035 --> 00:20:35,371
YOU'RE LIKE A SUPERNOVA JUST
BLOWING UP IN EVERY DIRECTION.

00:20:35,371 --> 00:20:38,174
AND THAT'S NOT GOOD IN BUSINESS.
YOU GOT TO HAVE A FOCUS.

00:20:38,174 --> 00:20:41,310
I THINK, PERSONALLY, THE ONLINE
STRATEGY WOULD BE BETTER.

00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,344
IT'S FULL MARGIN.

00:20:42,344 --> 00:20:45,214
YOU HAVE A BRAND
ON A SEARCH BASIS.

00:20:45,214 --> 00:20:48,117
YOU KNOW, NUT BARS LIKE CUBAN
WHO WANT TO EAT ROCKS --

00:20:48,117 --> 00:20:50,953
THIS IS WHAT HE GOES FOR.
THIS IS THE STUFF.

00:20:50,953 --> 00:20:52,988
THOSE HARD-CORE PEOPLE
ARE SEARCHING YOU OUT

00:20:52,988 --> 00:20:55,991
'CAUSE YOU OWN THE BRAND,
BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M HEARING.

00:20:55,991 --> 00:20:58,027
I'M HEARING A LOT OF,
YOU KNOW --

00:20:58,027 --> 00:21:00,062
A LOT OF DIFFERENT
DIRECTIONS.

00:21:00,062 --> 00:21:03,065
YOU'RE SCATTERED.
YOU ARE.

00:21:03,065 --> 00:21:04,967
AND THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU CAN'T FIX YOURSELF,

00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:07,002
OR MAYBE FIND A SHARK
THAT'S GONNA SIT DOWN

00:21:07,002 --> 00:21:08,303
AND HARNESS YOUR ENERGY.

00:21:08,303 --> 00:21:10,071
IT'S NOT GONNA BE ME.
I'M OUT.

00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:15,076
HERE'S MY ISSUE.
I DON'T THINK YOU DO ENOUGH.

00:21:15,076 --> 00:21:19,147
I THINK DENTAL HYGIENIST,
FITNESS INSTRUCTOR,

00:21:19,147 --> 00:21:22,383
MOM OF THREE, WIFE,
AND YOU HAVE PALEO.

00:21:22,383 --> 00:21:24,085
YOU COULD DO MORE
WITH YOUR DAY.

00:21:24,085 --> 00:21:27,222
I WORK AT 4:00 IN THE MORNING
TILL WHATEVER AT NIGHT.

00:21:27,222 --> 00:21:28,323
NO, I GOT IT. I --

00:21:28,323 --> 00:21:30,258
I MANAGE IT.
I HAVE THE DAY.

00:21:30,258 --> 00:21:32,994
EVERY MINUTE YOU SPEND
DOING ONE THING,

00:21:32,994 --> 00:21:36,197
YOU'RE MAKING A CONSCIOUS CHOICE
NOT TO DO ANOTHER THING.

00:21:36,197 --> 00:21:37,265
AND SO --

00:21:37,265 --> 00:21:39,167
AND I'M NOT SAYING
THAT'S RIGHT OR WRONG,

00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:41,035
BUT BE GREAT AT
ONE THING.

00:21:41,035 --> 00:21:42,337
DON'T TRY TO BE GREAT
AT MULTIPLE THINGS.

00:21:42,337 --> 00:21:44,939
I'M NOT SEEING THAT
IN YOUR PITCH TODAY.

00:21:44,939 --> 00:21:46,141
I'M SORRY. I'M OUT.

00:21:48,076 --> 00:21:50,944
I HAVE NO DOUBT YOU'RE GONNA
MAKE THIS THING WORK,

00:21:50,944 --> 00:21:52,279
BUT YOU ARE A LITTLE BIT
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

00:21:52,279 --> 00:21:55,382
YOU SHOULD HAVE CAME INTO
THIS ROOM LASER-FOCUSED,

00:21:55,382 --> 00:21:57,251
AND I CAN'T TAKE THIS RIDE
WITH YOU AT THE MOMENT.

00:21:57,251 --> 00:21:58,218
I'M OUT.

00:21:58,218 --> 00:22:00,287
MARK.

00:22:00,287 --> 00:22:02,222
I CAN DO THIS.

00:22:02,222 --> 00:22:07,060
I CAN BE LASER-FOCUSED,
AND IF IT REQUIRES ME GIVING UP

00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:10,164
TEACHING AND HYGIENE,
THEY ALL UNDERSTAND.

00:22:10,164 --> 00:22:12,132
I'M JUST A VERY LOYAL PERSON.
IT HAS TO DO WITH LOYALTY.

00:22:12,132 --> 00:22:13,233
Cuban: I KNOW YOU ARE.
WE CAN TELL.

00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:15,202
LOOK, I'M A BIG BELIEVER
IN PALEO, RIGHT?

00:22:15,202 --> 00:22:16,270
MM-HMM.

00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:18,305
I MEAN, I INVESTED IN
A COMPANY CALLED CHAPUL...

00:22:18,305 --> 00:22:19,406
OH, YES.

00:22:19,406 --> 00:22:21,308
...WHICH IS CRICKETS --
CRICKET-BASED PROTEIN.

00:22:21,308 --> 00:22:23,911
IT'S ABOUT AS PALEO
AS YOU CAN GET, RIGHT?
OH, YEAH.

00:22:23,911 --> 00:22:25,979
BUT THEY DON'T HAVE
DR. CORDAIN'S ENDORSEMENT.

00:22:25,979 --> 00:22:27,114
NO, THEY DON'T.
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:22:27,114 --> 00:22:28,282
THAT'S KIND OF
MY DISAPPOINTMENT,

00:22:28,282 --> 00:22:31,083
BECAUSE HAVING THAT AND
HAVING THE NAME IS PHENOMENAL

00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:32,952
AS AN OPPORTUNITY.

00:22:32,952 --> 00:22:34,086
AND WE WANT
TO GROW THE BRAND.

00:22:34,086 --> 00:22:35,288
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW TO GET THERE,

00:22:35,288 --> 00:22:37,290
AND THAT'S PART
OF THE PROBLEM,

00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:41,027
AND THAT'S WHY YOU'VE HEDGED
YOUR BET SO MANY DIFFERENT WAYS.

00:22:41,027 --> 00:22:43,429
YOU KNOW, HONESTLY,
I DIDN'T LIKE THE BARS.

00:22:43,429 --> 00:22:46,299
AND I THINK THEY HAVE
TOO MUCH SUGAR IN THEM.

00:22:46,299 --> 00:22:48,000
AND WE CAN TWEAK THAT.

00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,936
YOU KNOW,
I'VE ALREADY TALKED TO THE --

00:22:49,936 --> 00:22:52,004
I CAN'T COME IN
AND REDESIGN YOUR PRODUCT.

00:22:53,172 --> 00:22:55,107
AND FOR THOSE REASONS,
I'M OUT.

00:22:57,176 --> 00:22:59,078
Greiner:
EVERYBODY'S OUT, UNFORTUNATELY.

00:22:59,078 --> 00:23:00,313
WELL, THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.
I WISH YOU THE BEST.

00:23:00,313 --> 00:23:02,048
I WISH YOU
ALL THE BEST.
ALL RIGHT.

00:23:02,048 --> 00:23:03,115
GOOD LUCK, CAVEMAN.
YOU DID A GREAT JOB.

00:23:06,419 --> 00:23:08,354
DANG IT.

00:23:08,354 --> 00:23:10,122
Sledge: [ Crying ]
I JUST -- I FELT DISAPPOINTED.

00:23:10,122 --> 00:23:14,392
TOO MANY PEOPLE ARE COUNTING ON
THE SUCCESS OF THE PALEO DIET,

00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:16,428
AND I WILL NEVER GIVE UP,
BECAUSE,

00:23:16,428 --> 00:23:20,198
YOU KNOW, IF IT WEREN'T FOR
MY COMMUNITY AND MY FAMILY

00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:21,399
AND DR. CORDAIN,

00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:25,270
WE WOULDN'T BE WHERE WE ARE NOW,
AND I CAN'T GIVE UP ON THEM.

00:23:25,270 --> 00:23:27,405
I DON'T WANT TO GIVE UP ON THEM.

00:23:37,015 --> 00:23:40,018
Narrator: NEXT INTO THE TANK
IS AN ENTREPRENEUR

00:23:40,018 --> 00:23:42,420
WHO HOPES TO LURE THE SHARKS
WITH A BIG FISH.

00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:50,428
HELLO, SHARKS.
MY NAME IS GREG MYERSON.

00:23:50,428 --> 00:23:52,264
AND I'M FROM
WALLINGFORD, CONNECTICUT.

00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:54,398
MY COMPANY IS THE WORLD RECORD
STRIPER COMPANY,

00:23:54,398 --> 00:23:59,303
AND I'M SEEKING $75,000 IN
EXCHANGE FOR 20% OF MY COMPANY.

00:23:59,303 --> 00:24:02,239
SHARKS, I'M A FISHERMAN --
A DARN GOOD ONE.

00:24:02,239 --> 00:24:04,408
THAT'S BECAUSE I KNOW
THAT TO CATCH BIG FISH,

00:24:04,408 --> 00:24:05,943
YOU HAVE TO USE THE RIGHT BAIT.

00:24:05,943 --> 00:24:08,012
SO IF I'M FISHING FOR A SHARK,

00:24:08,012 --> 00:24:10,214
I'M PROBABLY GONNA USE
SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

00:24:10,214 --> 00:24:12,383
[ CUBAN LAUGHS ]

00:24:12,383 --> 00:24:13,417
THERE YOU GO.

00:24:13,417 --> 00:24:15,352
WHOA!

00:24:15,352 --> 00:24:17,054
YEAH, I FIGURED
YOU COULD USE SOME CASH.

00:24:17,054 --> 00:24:18,222
COME ON!

00:24:18,222 --> 00:24:20,958
Cuban:
THAT'S REAL MONEY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:24:20,958 --> 00:24:22,359
I'M THROWING THAT ONE BACK.
IT'S ONES.

00:24:22,359 --> 00:24:26,063
BUT WHEN I'M FISHING FOR FISH,
I USE MY VERY OWN PRODUCT --

00:24:26,063 --> 00:24:29,066
THE GREG MYERSON RattleSinker.

00:24:29,066 --> 00:24:31,936
THE RattleSinker ATTRACTS
BIG FISH TO YOUR HOOK

00:24:31,936 --> 00:24:34,405
BY MIMICKING THE SOUNDS
OF FISH'S FAVORITE FOODS.

00:24:34,405 --> 00:24:36,039
[ SINKER RATTLING ]
YOU HEAR THAT?

00:24:36,039 --> 00:24:39,242
TO A FISH, THAT'S THE SOUND
OF A DINNER BELL RINGING.

00:24:39,242 --> 00:24:41,377
MY PRODUCT HAS MADE ME

00:24:41,377 --> 00:24:44,247
ONE OF THE MOST FAMOUS FISHERMEN
IN THE WORLD, AND HERE'S WHY.

00:24:45,448 --> 00:24:51,220
SHARKS, THAT'S THE 82-POUND
WORLD-RECORD STRIPED BASS.

00:24:51,220 --> 00:24:52,322
YOU CAUGHT THAT?
YES, I DID --

00:24:52,322 --> 00:24:54,023
THE MOST SOUGHT-AFTER
WORLD RECORD

00:24:54,023 --> 00:24:55,124
IN ALL THE FISHING WORLD.

00:24:55,124 --> 00:24:56,159
Together: WOW.

00:24:56,159 --> 00:24:57,327
WOW, THAT COULD HAVE
KNOCKED OVER YOUR BOAT.

00:24:57,327 --> 00:25:00,263
SO, SHARKS, IT TOOK 29 YEARS
FOR THAT RECORD TO FALL

00:25:00,263 --> 00:25:01,931
AND ABOUT AN HOUR
FOR ME TO REEL IT IN.

00:25:01,931 --> 00:25:03,099
I HOPE IT DOESN'T TAKE ME
THAT LONG

00:25:03,099 --> 00:25:04,934
TO NET A DEAL
WITH ONE OF YOU.

00:25:04,934 --> 00:25:06,302
I GOT SOME PRODUCT
TO SHOW YOU.

00:25:10,173 --> 00:25:12,041
THANK YOU, GREG.
YES, SIR.

00:25:12,041 --> 00:25:13,209
OKAY.
[ SINKERS RATTLING ]

00:25:13,209 --> 00:25:14,344
IT'S KIND OF LIKE A RATTLE.

00:25:14,344 --> 00:25:16,079
YES, IT IS A RATTLE.

00:25:17,179 --> 00:25:19,381
DID YOU CATCH THAT FISH
USING THIS PRODUCT?

00:25:19,381 --> 00:25:21,049
YES, I DID.

00:25:21,049 --> 00:25:23,318
AND I HAVE THREE OTHER
WORLD RECORDS WITH THAT PRODUCT.

00:25:23,318 --> 00:25:25,120
STRIPED BASS IS
AMERICA'S FISH.

00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,989
IT'S THE MOST SOUGHT-AFTER
WORLD RECORD.

00:25:26,989 --> 00:25:28,023
WHY?
WHY?

00:25:28,023 --> 00:25:29,391
'CAUSE IT'S
THE EVERYMAN QUALITY.

00:25:29,391 --> 00:25:30,993
EVERYBODY CAN FISH FOR THIS.

00:25:30,993 --> 00:25:32,394
YOU DON'T NEED A YACHT.
YOU CAN FISH FROM SHORE.

00:25:32,394 --> 00:25:34,363
I GO TO MARTHA'S VINEYARD
EVERY SUMMER...

00:25:34,363 --> 00:25:35,364
YEAH?

00:25:35,364 --> 00:25:37,032
...AND THAT IS
THE FISHERMAN'S DREAM THERE,

00:25:37,032 --> 00:25:38,166
IS THE STRIPED BASS.
ABSOLUTELY.

00:25:38,166 --> 00:25:40,369
WELL, THIS PRODUCT CATCHES
MORE THAN STRIPED BASS.

00:25:40,369 --> 00:25:42,070
IT CATCHES ALL FISH.

00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:46,041
SO, WHY IS THIS THE BEST THING
TO USE IN THE WORLD...

00:25:46,041 --> 00:25:47,342
THAT'S
A GOOD QUESTION.

00:25:47,342 --> 00:25:49,144
...AND WHY DID THAT CATCH
THAT SIZE FISH?
GOOD QUESTION.

00:25:49,144 --> 00:25:51,013
I'VE BEEN A FISHERMAN
MY WHOLE LIFE.

00:25:51,013 --> 00:25:53,081
I STARTED FISHING WHEN
I WAS AGE 2 IN THE SEWER --

00:25:53,081 --> 00:25:55,117
AND PROBABLY A GOOD THING
I NEVER CAUGHT ANYTHING THERE.

00:25:55,117 --> 00:25:57,452
BUT AT 8, I MADE A FLY
OUT OF MY GRANDMOTHER'S PARROT.

00:25:57,452 --> 00:26:00,054
AND I HATED THAT THING.
IT ALWAYS ATTACKED ME.

00:26:00,054 --> 00:26:03,290
[ LAUGHTER ]
AND WHEN IT DIED, SHE SAID,
"WOULD YOU BURY IT FOR ME?"

00:26:03,290 --> 00:26:04,992
I SAID, "YEAH, YEAH, YEAH."

00:26:04,992 --> 00:26:07,161
I TIED 12 FLIES OUT OF IT.
I CAUGHT A TROUT.

00:26:07,161 --> 00:26:09,063
IT PUT ME ON THE FRONT PAGE
OF THE TOWN NEWSPAPER.

00:26:09,063 --> 00:26:10,331
[ LAUGHS ]
WITH HER DEAD PARROT?

00:26:10,331 --> 00:26:12,366
WITH THE FLIES I MADE
FROM HER FEATHERS, YEAH.

00:26:12,366 --> 00:26:13,968
I BECAME, LIKE,
A CELEBRITY IN TOWN.

00:26:13,968 --> 00:26:14,969
I HAD THIS BIG TROUT.

00:26:14,969 --> 00:26:16,037
OH, YOU ARE THE MAN.

00:26:16,037 --> 00:26:17,271
SO, WHEN I CAME UP WITH
THIS PRODUCT,

00:26:17,271 --> 00:26:19,940
I KNEW THAT THESE FISH
ARE SOUND-DRIVEN.

00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:21,942
THEY HUNT THROUGH SOUND
AND VIBRATION FIRST.

00:26:21,942 --> 00:26:23,044
THEY'RE ALL NEARSIGHTED.

00:26:23,044 --> 00:26:25,279
SO, YOU PULL IT ALONG...
YEP.

00:26:25,279 --> 00:26:27,014
...AND IT MAKES
THIS SOUND...
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:26:27,014 --> 00:26:28,315
...AS IT'S GOING ALONG
THE BOTTOM?
IT'S TRICKING THE FISH --

00:26:28,315 --> 00:26:30,084
ABSOLUTELY, IT'S TRICKING
THE FISH INTO THINKING

00:26:30,084 --> 00:26:32,019
THERE'S SOMETHING THERE
THAT IT ISN'T.

00:26:32,019 --> 00:26:33,287
WHY DID NOBODY
THINK OF THIS BEFORE?

00:26:33,287 --> 00:26:34,955
NOBODY'S AS SMART AS ME.

00:26:34,955 --> 00:26:36,257
GREG,
THIS IS JUST...
[ LAUGHS ]

00:26:36,257 --> 00:26:38,259
[ LAUGHS ] I LIKE YOU --
HUMBLE, THE HUMBLEBRAG.

00:26:38,259 --> 00:26:39,993
Greiner: HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN
SELLING THESE,

00:26:39,993 --> 00:26:41,061
AND WHERE
ARE YOU SELLING THESE?

00:26:41,061 --> 00:26:42,262
I JUST STARTED SELLING THEM
TWO YEARS AGO.

00:26:42,262 --> 00:26:43,329
WHEN I BROKE THE WORLD RECORD,

00:26:43,329 --> 00:26:45,031
I MEAN, THAT WAS
MY SECRET WEAPON FOR YEARS.

00:26:45,031 --> 00:26:46,966
YOU KNOW, I DID A LOT
OF RESEARCH ON THE SOUND.

00:26:46,966 --> 00:26:49,169
I GOT THE DECIBEL LEVELS DOWN.
IT'S PART OF MY PATENT CLAIMS.

00:26:49,169 --> 00:26:51,004
YOU HAVE A PATENT
